s338: Sixteen. Arrived in Guanzhong, executed Qin prince Ziying, massacred and burned Xianyang. Divided the realm, established feudal lords.
s339: Twenty-five. Divided Zhao into Dai state.
s340: Eighteen. Xiang Yu resented Rong, divided Qi into three states.
s341: Twenty-nine. Had a grudge with Xiang Yu, met him at Xi Xia, reconciled. Yu broke the agreement, divided Guanzhong into four states.
s342: Twenty-nine. Zang Chu followed entry, divided Yan into two states.
s343: Seventeen. Divided Wei into Yin state.
s344: Twenty. Divided Han into Henan state.
s367: Nine. Righteous Emperor year one. Feudal lords honored King Huai as Righteous Emperor.
s368: Seventeen. Xiang Ji self-established as Western Chu Hegemon King.
s388: Two. Moved capital to southern Chen.
s397: Twenty. King Tian Shi began, former Qi king.
s403: Thirty-one. King Han Guang began, former Yan king.
s404: Nineteen. King Wei Bao began, former Wei king.
s406: Twenty-two. King Han Cheng began, former Han general.
s431: Three. Feudal lords dismissed Xi Xia troops, all went to their states.
